summary:
Cersei: *Kidnaps Sansa*
Jon: *runs to KL to save his lov...sis... cousin*

Sansa: (...) and she was like "the North is as...
body:
Cersei: *Kidnaps Sansa*
Jon: *runs to KL to save his lov...sis... cousin*

Sansa: (...) and she was like "the North is as beautiful as you" and I was like "b*tch please, it's a little late for you to expect me to fall for this, you know?" and then she was all kind of "why are not everyone here worshipping me?" and all the time Jon was just "we need the dragons, we don't have time for politics,"... do you understand what I'm talking about?
Cersei: Totally! Did I ever tell you about when we met? She decided it would be so clever to be late and came riding on a dragon to show off her "power" and all I could think of was how this b*tch was making everyone waste time, I mean, I could be sitting on MY throne drinking wine and plotting the death of my enemies... but nooo... I was in that sh*thole waiting for this self-proclaimed queen to come riding her lizard as if everyone did not know they existed... for f*ck's sake! It was old news around here, you know?
Sansa: Yes, it looks like something she would do.
Jon: What the hell is going on here?
Sansa: Jon? What are you doing here?
Jon: Er... saving you?
Cersei: Ha, I told you he would come, I won!
Sansa: Well, how was I supposed to know?
Jon: Wait... you two bet if I was coming or not?
Jon: And you bet against me Sansa???
Sansa: 
Jon: You really don't have faith in me, do you?
Sansa: 
Sansa: Sorry?

tags: I've been seeing dany fans hating on Sansa
Sansa's the only one with some damn sense
summary:
You're Sansa, and your brother comes back to your home and tells you 
he's given your home and your kingdom to a foreign queen....
body:
You’re Sansa, and your brother comes back to your home and tells you he’s given your home and your kingdom to a foreign queen. Not only that, she’s a Targaryen. Her father killed your grandfather and uncle and as far as you know, her brother kidnapped, raped and murdered your aunt. Undoubtedly, you’ve heard all about how she likes to burn people alive. Your brother, mother and several of your loyal bannermen died fighting for your kingdom’s independence and your brother just gave it to a Targaryen. Without even bothering to consult anyone at home. While he was giving away your kingdom, you were busy trying to prepare for the coming winter by gathering supplies, supplies which are now woefully inadequate because this queen brought two armies and two dragons but no supplies. She could have brought supplies but she burned them.

I think you’d probably hate this foreign Targaryen queen too.
